  "texts": [
    "Vehicle PlacementWe use the language command and the scene map to generate the initial position.",
    "The scene map M follows the lane map form M = {n i, i = 1, 2, • • •, m}, where m is the number of lane nodes and the ith lane node n i = (x s, y s, x e, y e, c type) consists of lane starting position (x s, y s), ending position (x e, y e) and the lane type c type.",
    "The map range is cropped with the range of front 80m, left 20m and right 20m.",
    "Generally, we use the lane map from the ground-truth data.",
    "If the lane map does not exist, it is applicable to use a lane map estimation method like [44,45] to obtain the lane map.Given the language command, the LLM first extracts key placement attributes, including vehicle number, distance range, relative direction with the observer and direction of in autonomous driving dataset and the coordinates under Metashape's unified space."
  ],
